# Testing Rules

## Test Structure
Use bash scripts in [tests/](mdc:tests/) directory for API testing:

```bash
#!/bin/bash
# Source common utilities
SCRIPT_DIR="$(cd "$(dirname "${BASH_SOURCE[0]}")" && pwd)"
source "$SCRIPT_DIR/test-common.sh"

test_function_name() {
    print_subheader "Test Description"
    
    # Ensure proper authentication
    if [ -z "$TOKEN_VAR" ]; then
        login_function || return 1
    fi
    
    # Test implementation
    print_test "Test Action"
    local response
    response=$(curl_request "HTTP_METHOD" "$BASE_URL/api/endpoint" "request_data" "$TOKEN_VAR")
    
    local status_code="${response: -3}"
    local response_body="${response%???}"
    
    if test_status_code 200 "$status_code" "Test Name"; then
        test_json_field "$response_body" "success" "true" "Success Message"
        print_success "✅ Success Description"
    else
        print_error "❌ Error Description (Status: $status_code)"
    fi
}
```

## Test Coverage Requirements
- Test both authorized and unauthorized scenarios
- Include comprehensive validation testing
- Test edge cases and error conditions
- Test file uploads and multipart requests
- Verify response formats

